%% 3.1.12 Order Management — sequence (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin or Staff
    participant UI as UI (/orders)
    participant OC as Controller (OrderController)
    participant OS as Service (OrderService)
    participant Repo as Repository (Order Payment TransactionLog)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Actor->>UI: Open Order Management end of day
    UI->>OC: GET /api/Order/Search?status=PENDING&...
    OC->>OS: SearchOrderAsync
    OS->>Repo: Query orders + guardian + package
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    OS-->>OC: stuck pending list
    OC-->>UI: 200 — yellow Pending rows

    Actor->>UI: Identify guardian Nguyen B — verify in bank system

    Note over UI,OS: Manual mark Paid — nếu chưa có API: dùng PayOS webhook sau khi bank xác nhận hoặc thêm OrderService.ConfirmPaidAsync (admin only)

    opt Intended manual success path
        UI->>OC: POST admin reconcile e.g. confirm payment (future) OR rely on PayOS webhook
        OC->>OS: Mark order PAID + payment SUCCESS
        OS->>Repo: UPDATE Order Status PAID, TransactionLog
        Repo->>DB: UPDATE
        OS-->>OC: OrderDto green
        OC-->>UI: 200
    end

    alt Normal PayOS automation
        Note over OC,DB: PayOS webhook POST /api/Order/HandlePayOsWebhook sets PAID
    end

    Note over Actor,DB: BR12 — CancelOrderAsync: không revive CANCELLED; chuyển PAID→CANCELLED có refund path — không cho Pending lại từ terminal states (enforce trong service).
